## General CSS guidelines

- Use BEM class naming standards
- Prefer to nest elements and modifiers within the block (e.g. &__list or &--dark)
- Encourage atomic elements (e.g. notices, cards, badges) that are reusable in different areas
- Prefix atomic and BEM classes with givewp-
- Prefer to use scss instead of vanilla css

## CSS Variables
Reference the following style files to know which CSS variables to use when styling:
- Spacing (padding, margins, gaps, etc.): [spacing.css](mdc:node_modules/@givewp/design-system-foundation/css/spacing.css)
- Colors (font colors, backgrounds, etc.): [colors.css](mdc:node_modules/@givewp/design-system-foundation/css/colors.css)
- Fonts (weights, sizes, etc): [typography.css](mdc:node_modules/@givewp/design-system-foundation/css/typography.css)
